# Git Push After Changes

After making any code changes to this project, ALWAYS:

1. `git add` the changed files
2. `git commit` with a clear, descriptive message summarizing what changed and why
3. `git push` to origin

Do NOT wait for the user to ask — push automatically after every set of code modifications is complete.

If multiple related changes are made in sequence (e.g. updating agent.py then run_agent.sh), batch them into a single commit rather than committing each file separately.
